<div class="text-1">
<b>Friendy</b> was born from the idea that we are all human beings, and as such deserve the right to access modern money - cash is not king anymore!
<br>
<br>
So, what do you do when a homeless person asks you for some change? Do you A) Fumble in your pockets and say I left my wallet at home or B) Say,
sorry mate - I don't have/carry cash...
<br>
<br>
The inability for homeless people to gain access to modern financial services, reduces their ability to recieve donations from those wanting and
able to do so. That's why they always end up with sandwiches from Pret, rather than things they need, like toiletries.
<br>
<br>
For context, Cash Donations have reached a historic low of 7%. That means out of £5.4 Billion in donations made for 2020, only £3,780,000 were made to over
219,000 UK homeless people. Quick maths, that's £17.26 per person - for the <b>year.</b>
<br>
<br>
Friendy solves this by bridging the gap, using uniquely generated QR codes and your phone to donate directly to the person in front of you <b>100%</b>
goes to them. Now you don't need to worry saying you don't have cash just ask, <b>"What's your Friendy QR code mate?</b>
<br>
<br>
Thanks,
<br>
Chris and the Friendy Team.
